'''John Ashton''' (1830 – 25 December 1896) was a Welsh musician from [[Montgomeryshire]], who had worked as a policeman and shoemaker. He wrote a number of songs and hymns, including ''Trefeglwys'', written in 1857. His songs were published in ''Miwsig y Miloedd'',  ''Caniadau y Cysegr a'r Teulu,'' ''Llyfr Tonau Cynulleidfaol'', and ''Cerddor yr Ysgol Sabothol.'' He died in New Zealand, having emigrated there in 1874.<ref>{{cite web|title=John Ashton|url=http://yba.llgc.org.uk/en/s-ASHT-JOH-1830.html|author=Robert David Griffith|year=1959|website=Dictionary of Welsh Biography|publisher=National Library of Wales|accessdate=9 February 2016}}</ref>

